":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#logo"}},{"@type":"WebSite","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website","url":"https://roadtostudy.com","name":"Road to Study - Turkey University Guide for Students","alternateName":"Road to Study in Turkey","publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/careers-in-international-trade-and-export-in-turkey/#webpage","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/careers-in-international-trade-and-export-in-turkey/","name":"Careers in International Trade and Export in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-26T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-26T14:00:00+03:00","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#website"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Person","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat","url":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","@id":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","url":"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/9f5b866231ae7aed7a61015846c1f0ab6c5797b065ec200b93c5e9daa87897af?s=96&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g","caption":"Murat","inLanguage":"en-US"}},{"@type":"BlogPosting","headline":"Careers in International Trade and Export in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","datePublished":"2026-06-26T14:00:00+03:00","dateModified":"2026-06-26T14:00:00+03:00","articleSection":"Health and Safety","author":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/author/murat/","name":"Murat"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/#person"},"description":"Discover international trade and export careers in Turkey. Explore the opportunities available and learn how to shape your professional future in this dynamic field!","name":"Careers in International Trade and Export in Turkey - RoadtoStudy","@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/careers-in-international-trade-and-export-in-turkey/#richSnippet","isPartOf":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/careers-in-international-trade-and-export-in-turkey/#webpage"},"inLanguage":"en-US","mainEntityOfPage":{"@id":"https://roadtostudy.com/en/careers-in-international-trade-and-export-in-turkey/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With its strategic location, dynamic economy, and rich cultural heritage, Turkey offers significant opportunities in the field of international trade and export. In this article, you will find comprehensive information about international trade education in Turkey, the skills needed to start a career in export, career opportunities, the advantages and challenges of exporting, and internship and job prospects at international trade and export companies in Turkey.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-uluslararasi-ticaret-egitimi-neler-bilmeniz-gerekiyor" class="wp-block-heading">International Trade Education in Turkey: What You Need to Know</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">An education in international trade equips students with the ability to compete in global markets. Universities in Turkey offer a variety of programs in this field. The curriculum typically covers the following subjects:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Market Research</strong>: Understanding and analyzing global market dynamics.</li>
<li><strong>Trade Law</strong>: Learning the legal framework of international trade.</li>
<li><strong>Finance</strong>: Gaining knowledge about financing export and import transactions.</li>
<li><strong>Logistics Management</strong>: Managing the processes of international transportation and distribution of goods.</li>
</ul>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">You may also find our article on <a title="Careers in Translation and Language Services in Turkey" href="https://roadtostudy.com/turkiyede-ceviri-dil-hizmetleri-kariyeri/">Careers in Translation and Language Services in Turkey</a> helpful.</p>
<h2>How Much Does an Import-Export Specialist Earn?</h2>
<ul>
<li data-start="135" data-end="204">
<p data-start="137" data-end="204"><strong data-start="137" data-end="161">Entry-level specialist:</strong> 25,000 – 40,000 TRY → <strong data-start="183" data-end="202">≈ 610 – 976 USD</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="205" data-end="281">
<p data-start="207" data-end="281"><strong data-start="207" data-end="236">Mid-level (3–5 years of experience):</strong> 35,000 – 60,000 TRY → <strong data-start="258" data-end="279">≈ 854 – 1,463 USD</strong></p>
</li>
<li data-start="282" data-end="358">
<p data-start="284" data-end="358"><strong data-start="284" data-end="310">Experienced/Professional:</strong> 60,000 – 100,000 TRY → <strong data-start="333" data-end="356">≈ 1,463 – 2,439 USD</strong></p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="ihracat-kariyerine-adim-atmak-gerekli-beceriler-ve-yetkinlikler" class="wp-block-heading">Starting a Career in Export: Necessary Skills and Competencies</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Here are some fundamental skills that those wanting to start a career in export should possess:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Communication Skills</strong>: Being effective in both written and verbal communication.</li>
<li><strong>Analytical Thinking</strong>: The ability to analyze data and make strategic decisions.</li>
<li><strong>Cultural Awareness</strong>: Cultural sensitivity to interact effectively with different cultures.</li>
<li><strong>Marketing Knowledge</strong>: Knowing how to position products in the international market.</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="uluslararasi-ticaret-ve-ihracat-alaninda-kariyer-firsatlari" class="wp-block-heading">Career Opportunities in International Trade and Export</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are various career opportunities in the international trade and export sector in Turkey. These include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Export Manager</strong>: Enabling companies to expand into international markets.</li>
<li><strong>Market Analyst</strong>: Developing strategies by analyzing market trends.</li>
<li><strong>Logistics Specialist</strong>: Managing the transportation and distribution processes of goods.</li>
<li><strong>Trade Law Specialist</strong>: Overseeing legal processes related to international trade.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Practical Examples</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A market analyst can prepare reports on which markets a company should target by examining competition in a specific sector. These reports help managers make strategic decisions.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-ihracat-yapmanin-avantajlari-ve-zorluklari" class="wp-block-heading">Advantages and Challenges of Exporting in Turkey</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">There are many advantages and challenges to exporting in Turkey.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Advantages</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Strategic Location</strong>: Turkey serves as a bridge between Europe and Asia.</li>
<li><strong>Emerging Markets</strong>: Turkey offers opportunities to do business with emerging markets.</li>
<li><strong>Competitive Costs</strong>: The ability to manufacture at more affordable costs compared to other countries.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Challenges</h3>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Competition</strong>: High competition in international markets.</li>
<li><strong>Currency Exchange Rates</strong>: Increased costs due to currency fluctuations.</li>
<li><strong>Legal Regulations</strong>: The necessity of complying with the trade laws of different countries.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Practical Examples</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A Turkish exporter can develop hedging strategies to avoid being affected by fluctuations in currency exchange rates. Additionally, by complying with international trade regulations, they can avoid potential penalties.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyedeki-uluslararasi-ticaret-ve-ihracat-sirketleri-staj-ve-is-imkanlari" class="wp-block-heading">International Trade and Export Companies in Turkey: Internship and Job Opportunities</h2>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Many international trade and export companies in Turkey offer internship and job opportunities for students. These companies include:</p>
<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Large Exporting Firms</strong>: Companies operating in sectors such as textiles, food, and automotive.</li>
<li><strong>Consulting Firms</strong>: Firms that provide consulting services in the field of international trade.</li>
<li><strong>Logistics Companies</strong>: Firms that manage transportation and distribution processes.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Practical Examples</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">A student can intern at a large textile exporter to learn about production processes and strategies for entering international markets. This experience increases their chances of finding a job after graduation.</p>
<h2 id="sik-sorulan-sorular-faq" class="wp-block-heading">Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">Which universities should I choose for an international trade education in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Prestigious universities in Turkey such as Boğaziçi Üniversitesi, Koç Üniversitesi, and Sabancı Üniversitesi offer high-quality education in the field of international trade.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What skills do I need to start a career in export?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Skills such as communication, analytical thinking, cultural awareness, and marketing knowledge are important for starting a career in export.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What are the biggest challenges of exporting in Turkey?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">Competition, fluctuations in currency exchange rates, and the necessity to comply with legal regulations are among the biggest challenges of exporting in Turkey.</p>
<h3 class="wp-block-heading">What areas can I gain experience in during an internship?</h3>
<p class="wp-block-paragraph">During an internship, you can gain experience in areas like market research, logistics management, customer relations, and trade law.</p>
<h3 data-start="0" data-end="40">What are Turkey&#8217;s top exports?</h3>
<p data-start="41" data-end="136">Turkey&#8217;s top exports include automotive products, textiles, ready-to-wear apparel, electronics, and agricultural products.</p>
<h3 data-start="138" data-end="178">What major should I study for a career in export?</h3>
<p data-start="179" data-end="288">Majors such as Business Administration, International Trade, Foreign Trade, Economics, or Logistics are suitable for a career in export.</p>
<h3 data-start="290" data-end="336">What are Turkey&#8217;s export sectors?</h3>
<p data-start="337" data-end="458">The automotive, textile, ready-to-wear apparel, electronics, agricultural products, chemical, and machinery and equipment sectors are the largest export sectors.</p>', "wp_published_at" = '2026-06-26T11:00:00Z', "wp_modified_at" = '2026-03-16T19:53:41Z' WHERE "deleted_at" IS NULL AND "status" = 'published' AND "locale" = 'en' AND "slug" = 'careers-in-international-trade-and-export-in-turkey';
