om/en/job-opportunities-in-architecture-and-design-in-turkiye/#webpage"}}]}]}', "content_html" = '<p class="wp-block-paragraph">With its rich cultural heritage and historic structures, Türkiye offers significant potential in the fields of architecture and design. This article provides a comprehensive guide to the sector&#8217;s development, educational programs, internship and work opportunities, key cities, and networking events in Türkiye.</p>
<h2 id="turkiyede-mimarlik-ve-tasarim-sektorunun-gelisimi-ve-gelecegi" class="wp-block-heading">The Development and Future of the Architecture and Design Sector in Türkiye</h2>
<h4 data-start="364" data-end="400">Historical and Cultural Background</h4>
<ul data-start="401" data-end="721">
<li data-start="401" data-end="533">
<p data-start="403" data-end="533">The <strong data-start="403" data-end="433">Ottoman and Seljuk heritage</strong>, seen in mosques, social complexes, caravanserais, and bridges, provided an aesthetic foundation for contemporary architecture.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="534" data-end="616">
<p data-start="536" data-end="616">With the Republican era, <strong data-start="566" data-end="601">modernist and Western-influenced architecture</strong> gained momentum.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="617" data-end="721">
<p data-start="619" data-end="721">In the last 30 years, <strong data-start="636" data-end="704">global architectural trends, mass housing projects, and mega-structures</strong> have come to the forefront.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4 data-start="728" data-end="772">The Current State of Architecture and Design</h4>
<ul data-start="773" data-end="1415">
<li data-start="773" data-end="905">
<p data-start="775" data-end="905"><strong data-start="775" data-end="807">Urbanization and Urban Renewal</strong>: High-rise and renewal projects in metropolises like Istanbul, Ankara, and Izmir are driving the sector&#8217;s growth.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="906" data-end="1045">
<p data-start="908" data-end="1045"><strong data-start="908" data-end="933">Tourism-Focused Structures</strong>: Hotels, resorts, museums, and airports (e.g., Istanbul Airport) are attracting international attention.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1046" data-end="1180">
<p data-start="1048" data-end="1180"><strong data-start="1048" data-end="1080">Furniture and Interior Design</strong>: The İnegöl furniture sector and Istanbul-based design studios are competing in the European market.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1181" data-end="1292">
<p data-start="1183" data-end="1292"><strong data-start="1183" data-end="1206">Industrial Design</strong>: The contribution of Turkish designers is growing in the white goods, automotive, and electronics sectors.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1293" data-end="1415">
<p data-start="1295" data-end="1415"><strong data-start="1295" data-end="1322">International Competitions</strong>: Turkish architectural firms (like Tabanlıoğlu, Emre Arolat) are undertaking projects worldwide.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h4 data-start="1422" data-end="1458">Future Trends to Watch</h4>
<ul data-start="1459" data-end="2079">
<li data-start="1459" data-end="1539">
<p data-start="1461" data-end="1539"><strong data-start="1461" data-end="1488">Sustainable Architecture</strong>: High energy-efficient, eco-friendly buildings.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1540" data-end="1653">
<p data-start="1542" data-end="1653"><strong data-start="1542" data-end="1579">Smart Cities and Smart Buildings</strong>: Architectural solutions equipped with IoT, artificial intelligence, and automation systems.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1654" data-end="1766">
<p data-start="1656" data-end="1766"><strong data-start="1656" data-end="1696">Green Space and Public Space Design</strong>: Nature-friendly, human-centered living areas to counter dense urbanization.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1767" data-end="1887">
<p data-start="1769" data-end="1887"><strong data-start="1769" data-end="1827">Digital Design and BIM (Building Information Modeling)</strong>: Increased use of digitalization in project processes.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1888" data-end="1983">
<p data-start="1890" data-end="1983"><strong data-start="1890" data-end="1920">Cultural Heritage Preservation</strong>: Restoration and adaptive reuse of historical buildings.</p>
</li>
<li data-start="1984" data-end="2079">
<p data-start="1986" data-end="2079"><strong data-start="1986" data-end="2013">Globalization of Design</strong>: Turkish designers taking on more projects worldwide.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 id="turkiyede-mimarlik-okunur-mu" class="wp-block-heading">Should You Study Architecture in Türkiye?</h2>
<article class="text-token-text-primary w-full focus:outline-none scroll-mt-[calc(var(--header-height)+min(200px,max(70px,20svh)))]" dir="auto" tabindex="-1" data-turn-id="69d48caa-2d22-4ede-a5c7-9dca8415cd5d" data-testid="conversation-turn-12" data-scroll-anchor="true" data-turn="assistant">
<div class="text-base my-auto mx-auto pb-10 [--thread-content-margin:--spacing(4)] thread-sm:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(6)] thread-lg:[--thread-content-margin:--spacing(16)] px-(--thread-content-margin)">
<div class="[--thread-content-max-width:40rem] thread-lg:[--thread-content-max-width:48rem] mx-auto max-w-(--thread-content-max-width) flex-1 group/turn-messages focus-visible:outline-hidden relative flex w-full min-w-0 flex-col agent-turn" tabindex="-1">
